import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['miles'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Miles Driven')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['miles'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    avg_gas_prices = data.groupby(data['year'].dt.year)['gas'].mean()
    
    plt.plot(avg_gas_prices.index, avg_gas_prices.values)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Gas Price per Gallon')
    plt.title('What is the average gas price per gallon over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Average Gas Price'], loc='upper left')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    side_counts = data['side'].value_counts()
    ax = side_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'green', 'red', 'orange'])
    plt.title('What is the most common side of the road drivers are on?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Side of the Road')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Drivers')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax.legend(['Top', 'Right', 'Left', 'Bottom'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['miles'], data['gas'])
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Prices')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between miles driven and gas prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['year'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of years in the dataset?')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.axvline(data['year'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['year'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
